issue.body:
<!-- Thank you for your contribution! Please review https://github.com/ray-project/ray/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.rst before opening a pull request. -->

<!-- Please add a reviewer to the assignee section when you create a PR. If you don't have the access to it, we will shortly find a reviewer and assign them to your PR. -->

## Why are these changes needed?

We need a data structure that can track, for each replica (tenant), the prefixes of text it has seen and when, so that requests for new inputs can be routed to the replica with the best prefix-match “cache” hit. 

### Features:

- **LRU eviction** – To simulate the replicas' eviction policies, we must enable a least-recently-used eviction policy in our prefix tree. We enable efficient removals using a heap of timestamped nodes.  
- **Multi-tenant isolation** – Multiple replicas share the same tree; each node tracks per-tenant access times and char counts, so we can evict or match on a per-tenant basis.  
- **Concurrency model** [WIP] – We need to evaluate whether simple node-level locking on writes suffices or if a dual-tree swap approach (rotating read/write copies on a timer) would yield better performance under high concurrency.


<!-- Please give a short summary of the change and the problem this solves. -->

refactor(customerRepository): Create interface CustomerRepository

Change the ClienteRepository implementation to an interface called CustomerRepository and its implementation to CustomerRepositoryAdapter to avoid 'mapper hell',  which was perceived in the code, and to isolate the domain as well.

chore(gitignore): Remove the folder /target from Git

- Change ./target (wrong) by /target

refactor(CartaoDeCreditoRepository) Refactor repository to domain interface + adapter to encapsulate mappers and simplify testing.

The infrastructure class CartaoDeCreditoRepository was refactored into CartaoRepository - now an interface in the domain layer, with its implementation in the CartaoDeCreditoRepositoryAdapter class. This change aims to:

- Avoid the 'mapper hell' that was occurring in tests
- Encapsulate toDomain and toEntity mappers within the repository
- Isolate the domain through the interface

Merge pull request #1 from claston/feat/improve-customer-domain
